title: in attack of youtubers
body:
it bothers me that youtubers refuse to accept responsibility for what they inspire their young and/or vulnerable audience to say and do. all other celebrities are aware that what they say affects people. they’re careful about what they say and do, because they understand their responsibility.

youtubers refuse to do so. they squirm and beg not to be taken seriously. they whine about how they feel such a great responsibility and it’s unfair and they don’t want it. they write off children and “idiots” and pretend their audiences are only responsible, reasonable adults.

but let’s be honest - the only reason these people have an audience is children and vulnerable people. they are the ones who buy merch. who actually share your videos. who like, comment, and subscribe. who will defend you whatever you’re accused of. who will stay subscribed whatever you do. who will excuse everything by blindly repeating that “everyone makes mistakes”. they will let you get away with everything, but there is a price to be paid: they will also listen to you.

and youtubers act like absolute babies about that. “i want a devoted audience, i want thousands of views, i want my merch bought at twice the price it’s worth, but i will never accept that all this comes at a price. it’s unfair”

stop pretending to be a victim in this situation. i see you, rich people, filming in the one tiny room in your house designed to look ordinary. i see your desperate attempts to continue to seem relatable and weak. how can you, 25-30 years old, let 12-year-old girls and lonely adults call you “cute lil beans who need to be protected”? have you no shame?

you rely on these people, you do your best to make them love you, choose you, and give you their pocket money, but when they say what you taught them to say and do what you taught them to do, you turn your back on them. “it was just a joke”, you say. “only idiots wouldn’t see that i wasn’t serious”, you say. “please don’t take anything i say seriously”, you say.

i hate that.

body:
So I decided to make this tumblr account to post things about Colby Brock and Sam Golbach.

I love them both so much. They’re my inspiration. They taught me and inspired me so much.

I wanna be like them someday. I wanna be braver and step out of my comfort zone. I wanna be out going and talk to many people.

I wanna have a friendship like theirs someday. Their bond are so strong. They’re always there for each other. Perfect bestfriend, I would kill to have ❤

Sam and Colby may you two always be blessed ❤

Take chances and go beyond the norm

Sam and Colby may you two always be blessed ❤

Take chances and go beyond the norm

Sat. March 30th, 2019. 5:51 PM
